name: Sia-UI
description: A Graphical Frontend for Sia - https://sia.tech

packageJSON.name: Sia-UI
packageJSON.description: A UI application for interfacing with Sia

scripts.clean: rm -rf release doc/Sia-UI node_modules Sia config.json **/*.swp npm-debug.log
scripts.fresh: npm run clean && npm install && npm start
scripts.test: npm run lint && npm run build && npm run test-args

releases.name: Sia-UI v1.1.0
releases.body:
This is a minor release to accompany the v1.1.0 release of Sia.

It contains minor fixes, such as adding an allowance confirmation dialog and changing the keyboard shortcuts to be non-global.

Thanks to @BitcoinErrorLog for contributing to this release!

releases.name: Sia-UI v1.0.4 LTS
releases.body: This is an LTS release that accompanies the standard v1.0.4 release. The code is identical, except that this release is bundled with the v1.0.4-LTS release of Sia. Please read our [LTS page](http://sia.tech/lts) describing how LTS releases of Sia will work.

releases.name: Sia-UI v1.0.4
releases.body:
This is a patch release that adds the Logs plugin, which allows users to view Sia's various log files without leaving the UI. The Logs plugin is hidden by default, but can be revealed via `Ctrl+Shift+L`.
This release also includes bug fixes and style changes to the Files plugin, among other minor bug fixes.

This release uses the v1.0.4 release of Sia.

releases.name: Sia-UI v1.0.3
releases.body:
This is a patch release that improves startup/shutdown behavior, adds functionality to the Files plugin, and fixes many minor bugs.

Signatures are now included in UI releases. They can be verified using the [Sia developer key](https://github.com/NebulousLabs/Sia/blob/3dc47979a53744f5a32c8f3fb355006455d81ac0/api/daemon.go#L75):

```
openssl dgst -sha256 -verify sia.pem -signature Sia-UI-*.sig Sia-UI-*.zip
```

This release uses the v1.0.3 release of Sia.

Thanks to @lolsteve for contributing to this release!

releases.name: Sia-UI v1.0.2
Sia-UI v1.0.1
releases.body:
This is a patch release that fixes price estimation when calculating the allowance in the Files plugin. The old estimation algorithm was susceptible to overpriced hosts dominating the average. The new algorithm ignores outliers when estimating the average host price.
It also fixes a permissions error that prevented Windows users from adding storage folders.

This release uses the 1.0.0 release of Sia.

releases.name: Sia-UI v1.0.0
releases.body:
Today we are releasing version 1.0 of Sia-UI.

The UI has undergone a complete rewrite in React+Redux, thanks to the efforts of @johnathanhowell and @droghio.

@droghio has written a guide for updating to v1.0.0, available [here](http://forum.sia.tech/topic/221/sia-v1-0-upgrade-guide).

The most important thing to bear in mind is that the UI will now store its siad data (e.g. the blockchain and your wallet) in a globally shared directory: `ApplicationSupport` on OSX, `%APPDATA%` on Windows, and `~/.config` on Linux.

Note that Sia-UI v1.0.0 is not held to the compatibility promise of Sia v1.0.0. In addition, Sia-UI binaries and release tags will not be signed until automatic updates are implemented (as they are in Sia).

Thanks to everyone who contributed to this release, especially the usuals in our Slack #contributors channel who gave feedback on the UI.

releases.name: Sia-UI v0.5.2
releases.body: This is a patch release to accompany the latest Sia release, v0.5.2. It includes changes to the taskbar and closing behavior, as well as a few minor bugfixes.

releases.name: Sia-UI v0.5.1
releases.body: This is a patch release that fixes various minor bugs. The most notable bug caused selected files to be sorted incorrectly.

releases.name: Sia-UI v0.5.0
releases.body:
Sia has matured greatly since our last stable release, v0.4.8. Most notably, we have added a new file browser with fully navigable directory structure. (Thanks to @pmknutsen for his contributions to the Files plugin!) See the corresponding release of Sia v0.5.0 for a more detailed breakdown.

Remember, this release is expected to be somewhat unstable. Take precautions to protect your data by backing up your wallet passphrase and file (wallet/wallet.json) and your .sia files (in the renter directory). Patches to the v0.5.x release will address issues as they arise, so you are encourage to check for a new release if you are experiencing problems.

We look forward to seeing what you do with Sia!

releases.name: Sia-UI v0.4.8-beta
releases.body:
This is a patch release that adds file searching functionality.
Note that this release uses the latest version of Sia (v0.4.8), which is incompatible with v0.3.3.x nodes.

Thanks to @pmknutsen for contributing to this release.

releases.name: Sia-UI v0.4.7-beta
releases.body: This is a patch release to accompany the latest Sia release, v0.4.5. No significant changes were made to the UI.

releases.name: Sia-UI v0.4.6-beta
releases.body: This is a patch release that fixes the UI not spawning siad properly. When launching the UI, you should now wait until the "siad started!" notification appears. (Note that if siad is already running, this notification will not be displayed.)

releases.name: Sia-UI v0.4.5-beta
releases.body:
This is a patch that fixes a bug where config.json would occasionally become undefined.

Thanks to @pmknutsen for his work on this.

releases.name: Sia-UI v0.4.4
releases.body:
Version v0.4.4 brings a fresh reskinning of the UI, along with a new "Add Folder" button in the Files view that allows you to easily upload an entire directory. Both of these were implemented by @pmknutsen -- fantastic work!

Also thanks to @bitspill, who implemented some less prominent tweaks, such as not displaying the wallet balance in the Overview before it has been unlocked.

We are really excited to see these contributions from the developer community. We fully embrace the open-source paradigm, and want to encourage such contributions as much as possible. Sia is a big project, so there's lots of things you can work on. If you spot a bug or a missing feature, please open an issue, hit us up on Slack, or submit a PR, and we'll work with you to make Sia better for everyone.

releases.name: Sia-UI v0.4.3
releases.body: This is a minor release to accompany Sia v0.4.3. The Wallet view is more user-friendly now; it won't display your balance until you unlock the wallet (previously, a balance of 0 was displayed). More significant updates will accompany v0.4.4.

releases.name: Sia-UI v0.4.2
releases.body:
Wallet initialization is now displayed correctly on small resolutions screens, featuring a smaller font and a scrollbar. The build process for Mac has been repaired. 'siad' has been updated from v0.4.1 to v0.4.2.

'siad' still does not exit when the UI gets closed, because it was causing database corruption problems. We expect the database corruption issues to be resolved for v0.4.3, which should be released in the next two weeks.

releases.name: Sia-UI v0.4.1
releases.body:
This is the first release of the New Sia UI. (Version numbers are always pegged to the version of Sia they are compatible with; in this case that is [Sia v0.4.1](https://github.com/NebulousLabs/Sia/releases/tag/v0.4.1-beta).)

This UI is developed around a plugin-based architecture that should cleanly delineate functionality, as well as allowing anyone to drop in their own plugin.

The bulk of the UI was written by @Mingling94 during his Summer '15 internship with Nebulous. Props to him! Hope you like it.
